Date:  0/0/1887
Source:  Handbook NZ Mines
Author:
Vol / Page:  215
Edition:
Quote:  ... ground-sluicing is now more generally adopted, unless where the ground is very deep. The sand is usually washed over the wide sluice-boxes, covered with different materials, such as plush, green baize, coir matting, and copper-plates coated with quicksilver, which catch the fine gold, while the lighter particles float away.
